      <akn:section eId="sec_4_1451_05">
        <akn:num>4-1451.05</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Parental rights.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-1451_05_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Notwithstanding § 4-1406(b) [(b) repealed], there shall be no 72-hour waiting period prior to relinquishment of parental rights under this chapter. A relinquishment of parental rights shall take place upon surrender. Upon CFSA’s receipt of the statement required by § 4-1451.02(d) and assuming physical custody, CFSA shall assume immediate care, custody, and control of the surrendered newborn.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-1451_05_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A relinquishment of parental rights under this chapter may be revoked and parental rights restored in accordance with § 4-1406(c) and (d); provided, that:</akn:p></akn:content>
